Look at the bottom of that table. The GCAL 3.00ct D-FL at **[$22,470](https://www.bluenile.com/diamond-details/27891184?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blue_nile_reviews)** is almost exactly double the D-IF IGI stones sitting above it at **[$11,770](https://www.bluenile.com/diamond-details/29116879?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blue_nile_reviews)**–**[$12,200](https://www.bluenile.com/diamond-details/27512147?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blue_nile_reviews)**. That is a $10,000+ premium for FL over IF at 3ct — for a distinction that is invisible to the naked eye and requires specialized equipment to detect even in a controlled lab environment. At 3ct, the **Bigger Window Effect** does become relevant — larger table facets make inclusions theoretically more visible — but IF is already 100% eye-clean at 3ct in a round brilliant. You do not need FL.

